resource.name: SDOT Street Use Sign-In Data
resource.description: Data from Seattle Department of Transportation Street Use Division Applicant Services Sign In system. Data collection started in May 2009. Data is used to run the SUSI application, which alerts permit reviewers by type of review that an applicant is at the counter. Applicants come to the counter to pay fees, get coaching, apply for permits, and extend permits for a wide variety of private uses of the right of way. The data can be used to calculate changes over time for visit volumes, volumes by category, wait times, and service times. Wait time data prior to 2013 is unreliable. Check-in categories changed in July 2013 and February 2014. Category information is unreliable prior to February 2014. Prior to that February 2014, customers self-selected the category. Post February 2014, screeners selected the category.
resource.attribution: City of Seattle Department of Transportation Street Use Division

Calculated field: TimeReachedTime minus TimeInTime in minutes.

Raw data: Visit reasons updated in July 2013 and February 2014. Prior to February 2014, visitors self-selected. Post February 2014, qualified screeners made the selections. Data unreliable prior to February 2014. Exclude Staff Use Only -- this checks visitors in for screening. After screening, customers are signed back in for the a specific visit reason. Counting both would inflate visit counts. Visitors may check in more than once for other categories since they may need to see multiple reviewer types depending on the complexity of their project(s).

Raw data: Status of the customer at the time the data was last uploaded. If the date is more than a day older than the data and the status is not Completed, a button was not clicked. All visitors leave Street Use by 5:00 PM each day.

Calculated field: Calculates TimeCompletedTime minus TimeReachedTime in hours. Used for calculating service times longer than 2 hours.
